com.terradue.ssegrid.sagaext
Class ProcessingRegistry

java.lang.Object
  com.terradue.ssegrid.sagaext.ProcessingRegistry

public class ProcessingRegistry
extends java.lang.Object

This class acts as the processing shelf and manager. It registers the processing described by a JSDLDocument as template using the method registerProcessing(JSDLDocument). A registered processing template is requested using #getJSDLFromProc(int) that returns the JSDL document that the JobFactory object may transform into a JobDescription to be used then by JobService for creating Jobs. At creation if the boolean syncWithDisk is set to true in the constructor ProcessingRegistry(boolean), the processing registry synchronizes the operations registerProcessing(JSDLDocument) and #unregisterProcessing(int) with the file system under the path set by the VM property ${gai.deploy.process.path}. Therefore, when a JSDLDocument is registered, the processing registry places a file copy of the template under a specific path, and deletes it when unregistered. It also loads the existing JSDL file in the path enabling the recovering of the registered processing template in case of crash. If the boolean is set to false, no synchronization is performed.

registerProcessing

public java.lang.String registerProcessing(JSDLDocument template)
                                    throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                                           java.io.IOException,
                                           JSDLNotApplicableException,
                                           JSDLException
Registers template and returns its identifier. The template is validated beforehand. If the synchronization with the disk is enabled, the operations write a file copy of the JSDL template under 
${GAI_DEPLOYPROCESS_PATH}\/*{process_id}*\/JSDLTemplate.xml
 and creates the directory if not present.

Parameters:
template - object implementing the JSDLDocument interface and that contains the processing template. JSDLFactory may create such an object from a physical file.
Returns:
the processing identifier that is generated from the JobName element of the JSDL document. If JobName is not present, a random UUID is generated.
Throws:
java.io.FileNotFoundException - is thrown when the path specified by the environment variable ${WPS_DEPLOY_PATH} does not exist or is not readable.
java.io.IOException - is thrown if any I/O error occurs during operations or reading or writing data on the disk
JSDLNotApplicableException - is thrown if the JSDL template is invalid
JSDLException

unregisterProcessing

public void unregisterProcessing(java.lang.String ProcID)
                          throws java.util.NoSuchElementException,
                                 java.io.FileNotFoundException
Removes the processing template identified by procID from the registry. If synchronization with the disk is enabled, the file under 
${GAI_DEPLOYPROCESS_PATH}\/*{process_id}*\/JSDLTemplate.xml
 id deleted from the disk but not the directory.

Parameters:
ProcID - the identifier of the processing template to remove
Throws:
java.util.NoSuchElementException - if the processing identifier provided does not correspond to any registered processing.
java.io.FileNotFoundException
